<!-- Stage detail panel -->
<div class="panel stage-detail">
  <div class="panel-header">
    <span class="panel-title" id="stageTitle">Stage 01 · Synthetic Fund Generator</span>
    <span class="panel-title mono" id="stageMeta">EMERALD CAPITAL PARTNERS I</span>
  </div>
  <div class="stage-content" id="stageContent">
    <!-- Stage 0 default -->
    <div id="view-0">
      <div class="stage-eyebrow">STAGE 01 / SYNTHETIC GENERATION</div>
      <h2>A €500M Irish QIAIF, generated on demand</h2>
      <p>The fund is not pulled from a fixture file — it is generated procedurally from a persona-driven schema. Subscriptions, redemptions, positions, NAV history, FX exposure, and stress-scenario flows all derive from the controls on the left. This is the strength of synthetic data: every edge case the real world might throw at the engine is reproducible on demand.</p>

      <div class="stat-grid">
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="stat-label">AUM</div>
          <div class="stat-val cyan" id="kpi-aum">€500.0M</div>
          <div class="stat-sub">prior NAV strike</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="stat-label">Positions</div>
          <div class="stat-val" id="kpi-pos">147</div>
          <div class="stat-sub">across 3 asset classes</div>
        </div>
