    <!-- Stage 2: Semantic layer -->
    <div id="view-2" class="hidden">
      <div class="stage-eyebrow">STAGE 03 / SEMANTIC LAYER</div>
      <h2>Every entity named once, with units and lineage</h2>
      <p>This is what Fusion calls the common semantic layer — and what JPM identified as the foundation of being LLM-ready. Below is our YAML-defined semantic model for the swing-pricing workflow. Every field has a definition, unit, identifier, and source lineage. The Builder is only allowed to reason over this model; the Anomaly Agent is only allowed to compare against it.</p>

      <div class="tabs">
